  "texts": [
    "Swin-PANet [76] is a dual supervision network structure proposed by Zhihao Liao et al.",
    "Swin-PANet is made up of two networks: a prior attention network and a hybrid transformer network.",
    "The prior attention network applies the sliding window-based subattention mechanism to the intermediate supervision network, whereas the hybrid transformer network aggregates the features of the jump connection and the prior attention network and refines the boundary details.",
    "GlaS [72] and MoNuSeg [73] yield better results.",
    "DS-TransUNet [77] is constructed upon the SwinTransformer framework and enhances feature representation with a dual-scale encoder."
  ],
